      "body": "<h3>Greptile Summary</h3>\n\nThis PR adds a `--copy HOST_PATH:IMAGE_PATH` flag to `mise oci build` and a matching `[[oci.copy]]` TOML primitive. Each source (file, directory, or symlink) is emitted as an independent, content-addressed layer annotated with `dev.mise.copy=<image path>`, inserted after tool layers in the manifest.\n\n- **`OciCopy` struct and parsing** (`src/oci/mod.rs`): `FromStr` uses `rsplit_once(':')` to preserve Windows drive letters in the host path; `validate_image_path` enforces absolute, dot-free image paths; config-file `[[oci.copy]]` entries and CLI copies are accumulated in most-specific-first order via `fill_defaults_from`.\n- **`build_layer_from_path`** (`src/oci/layer.rs`): dispatches on actual-directory vs file/symlink using `symlink_metadata` (preserving symlinks rather than following them); parent directory entries are synthesised by the existing `prefix_parents` helper; two new unit tests cover the file-to-exact-path and directory-contents-beneath-path scenarios.\n- **Builder integration** (`src/oci/builder.rs`): config copies chain before CLI copies; each is validated and built in step 5, then written to the manifest between tool layers and the dotfiles layer; `push` and `run` hardcode `copy: vec![]` so config `[[oci.copy]]` entries are still honoured there even though no CLI flag is exposed.\n\n<h3>Confidence Score: 4/5</h3>\n\nSafe to merge; the new copy primitive is well-isolated and the existing layer pipeline is unchanged. A few minor edge cases (root `/` image path, symlink size field) are worth tidying but none affect the happy path.\n\nThe core logic \u2014 parsing, validation, tar construction, annotation \u2014 is correct and well-tested. The only real gap is that validate_image_path permits `/` as an image destination for directory copies, which silently produces a root-level extraction instead of an error. The fill_defaults_from docstring omits the Vec-accumulation semantics for copy, which could mislead future contributors. Both are straightforward fixes and don't affect normal usage.\n\nsrc/oci/mod.rs \u2014 validate_image_path root-path edge case and fill_defaults_from docstring gap. src/oci/layer.rs \u2014 symlink size field inconsistency.\n\n<h3>Important Files Changed</h3>\n\n\n\n\n| Filename | Overview |\n|----------|----------|\n| src/oci/mod.rs | Introduces OciCopy struct, FromStr parser (rsplit_once for Windows-path safety), validate_image_path, and adds copy Vec to OciConfig. fill_defaults_from accumulates copy entries from all config layers, which is correct behavior but differs from the \"first-Some-wins\" semantics documented for other fields. |\n| src/oci/layer.rs | Adds build_layer_from_path dispatching on actual dir vs file/symlink using symlink_metadata; parent directories are correctly synthesized by prefix_parents. Two new unit tests cover file-to-exact-path and directory-contents-beneath-path scenarios. |\n| src/oci/builder.rs | Config copies (self.oci.copy) are chained before CLI copies (opts.copy), then built and written to the manifest after tool layers but before dotfiles. Each copy layer gets a dev.mise.copy annotation with the image path. Validate is called per copy at build time. |\n| src/cli/oci/build.rs | Adds --copy Vec<OciCopy> flag wired into BuildOptions; straightforward change. |\n| e2e/oci/test_oci_build_slow | Step 10 adds e2e coverage for --copy and [[oci.copy]], asserting layer annotations and tar contents for both file and directory cases. Ordering assertion (config copy before CLI copy) matches the builder's chain order. |\n| docs/dev-tools/mise-oci.md | Adds --copy flag documentation and [[oci.copy]] TOML examples; copy semantics section is accurate. |\n\n\n<!-- greptile_other_comments_section -->\n\n<a href=\"https://app.greptile.com/ide/claude-code?prompt=Fix%20the%20following%203%20code%20review%20issues.%20Work%20through%20them%20one%20at%20a%20time%2C%20proposing%20concise%20fixes.%0A%0A---%0A%0A%23%23%23%20Issue%201%20of%203%0Asrc%2Foci%2Fmod.rs%3A179%0A**%60fill_defaults_from%60%20docstring%20doesn't%20cover%20the%20copy%20Vec**%0A%0AThe%20method-level%20doc%20says%20%22first%20value%20encountered%20wins%22%20and%20mentions%20only%20map%20fields%20%28env%2C%20labels%29%20as%20exceptions%20to%20the%20scalar%20%22first-Some-wins%22%20rule.%20The%20%60copy%60%20Vec%20uses%20a%20third%20semantic%20%E2%80%94%20unconditional%20accumulation%20%E2%80%94%20which%20isn't%20documented%20here.%20A%20future%20contributor%20reading%20only%20the%20docstring%20would%20expect%20that%20the%20most-specific%20config's%20%60copy%60%20list%20wins%20outright%2C%20not%20that%20all%20layers'%20lists%20are%20merged.%20Worth%20adding%20a%20sentence%20like%20%22For%20Vec%20fields%20%28copy%29%2C%20entries%20from%20all%20configs%20are%20accumulated%20in%20most-specific-first%20order.%22%0A%0A%23%23%23%20Issue%202%20of%203%0Asrc%2Foci%2Fmod.rs%3A61-71%0A**%60validate_image_path%60%20should%20reject%20%60%22%2F%22%60%20as%20an%20image%20destination**%0A%0A%60%22%2F%22%60%20passes%20both%20existing%20guards%20but%20trims%20to%20an%20empty%20target%2C%20silently%20routing%20a%20directory%20copy%20into%20%60build_layer_from_dir%28host_path%2C%20%22%22%2C%20owner%29%60%20and%20placing%20its%20contents%20directly%20at%20the%20image%20root.%20Catching%20this%20early%20gives%20a%20clear%20error%20rather%20than%20a%20confusing%20tar%20layout.%0A%0A%60%60%60suggestion%0Afn%20validate_image_path%28path%3A%20%26str%29%20-%3E%20Result%3C%28%29%2C%20String%3E%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20if%20!path.starts_with%28'%2F'%29%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20return%20Err%28format!%28%22copy%20image%20path%20must%20be%20absolute%20%28got%20%7Bpath%3A%3F%7D%29%22%29%29%3B%0A%20%20%20%20%7D%0A%20%20%20%20if%20path.trim_matches%28'%2F'%29.is_empty%28%29%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20return%20Err%28format!%28%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%22copy%20image%20path%20must%20not%20be%20the%20root%20%60%2F%60%20%28got%20%7Bpath%3A%3F%7D%29%22%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%29%29%3B%0A%20%20%20%20%7D%0A%20%20%20%20if%20path.split%28'%2F'%29.any%28%7Cpart%7C%20part%20%3D%3D%20%22.%22%20%7C%7C%20part%20%3D%3D%20%22..%22%29%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20return%20Err%28format!%28%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%22copy%20image%20path%20must%20not%20contain%20%60.%60%20or%20%60..%60%20components%20%28got%20%7Bpath%3A%3F%7D%29%22%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%29%29%3B%0A%20%20%20%20%7D%0A%20%20%20%20Ok%28%28%29%29%0A%7D%0A%60%60%60%0A%0A%23%23%23%20Issue%203%20of%203%0Asrc%2Foci%2Flayer.rs%3A154-156%0A**%60size%60%20field%20is%20set%20from%20%60metadata.len%28%29%60%20for%20symlinks%20but%20is%20silently%20ignored**%0A%0AFor%20a%20symlink%2C%20%60metadata.len%28%29%60%20on%20Linux%20returns%20the%20length%20of%20the%20link-target%20string%2C%20not%20zero.%20The%20%60Entry%60%20is%20constructed%20with%20this%20value%2C%20but%20the%20%60EntryKind%3A%3ASymlink%60%20arm%20in%20%60build_layer_from_entries%60%20always%20calls%20%60header.set_size%280%29%60%2C%20overriding%20it.%20This%20is%20harmless%20today%20but%20is%20a%20misleading%20field%20value%20if%20%60Entry%60%20is%20ever%20reused.%20Setting%20%60size%3A%200%60%20for%20symlinks%20when%20constructing%20the%20entry%20would%20make%20the%20intent%20explicit.%0A%0A&repo=jdx%2Fmise&pr=10952&platform=github\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixAllInClaudeDark.svg?v=6\"><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixAllInClaude.svg?v=6\"><img alt=\"Fix All in Claude Code\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixAllInClaude.svg?v=6\"></picture></a>\n\n<sub>Reviews (1): Last reviewed commit: [\"feat(oci): add reproducible host path co...\"](https://github.com/jdx/mise/commit/aee14f0cfbe4bef96ec3f35c0e0668cec044b164) | [Re-trigger Greptile](https://app.greptile.com/api/retrigger?id=43574729)</sub>",
